    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hundreds of services from Google are available to consumers as API. Every API has a specific purpose. Over a period of time, google keeps clubbing these API endpoints (a url/place where a service is available), cleaning their code and improving the capabilities of these services. Therefore, sometimes it looks endpoint or pip package is the same, but its API name is different. Recently when google clubbed their many AI APIs they are moved under VertexAI and API endpoint changed to aiplatform.googleapi.com. To bring some clarity for my own sake and some of you may like this, I wrote this article.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
